  "body": "After 1-3 hours of running coredns seems to accumulate a bunch about 28k of not closed UDP connections. \r\nHere is the part of the Corefile that sets up proxying. These addresses are not mentioned anywhere else in the corefile. \r\n```\r\nproxy . 169.254.169.254:53 8.8.8.8:53\r\n```\r\n\r\nOpen connections\r\n```\r\nlsof -p COREDNS_PID\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:58421->8.8.8.8:domain\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:40939->8.8.8.8:domain\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:32799->169.254.169.254:domain\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:40991->8.8.8.8:domain\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:57377->8.8.8.8:domain\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:49185->169.254.169.254:domain\r\nUDP coredns_server_ip:33846->169.254.169.254:domain\r\n```\r\n\r\nMetrics screenshot:\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4558851/21608861/fed29bc2-d1b6-11e6-90e4-e749b87baece.png)\r\n\r\nSo it really looks like it is something in proxy middleware.",
